Hiroi Ueda patented the selfie stick in 1983 while working for camera company Minolta . 
  He came up with the idea after struggling to take 'selfies' with his family in Europe . 
  The 'extender stick' was designed to be used with compact cameras at the time . 
  Mr Ueda says he first invented the gadget in the 1980s while on holiday . 
  Selfie sticks have been banned from a number of tourist venues . 
 